WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.201 --> 00:00:02.637
[R.J.] <i>Previously on </i>
R.J. Decker <i>...</i>

2
00:00:02.770 --> 00:00:04.137
Don't try to eat it
through the wrapper.

3
00:00:04.271 --> 00:00:05.607
Today could be the last day
of my trial.

4
00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:07.742
meaning I could be going home
in a few hours. or--

5
00:00:07.876 --> 00:00:09.009
Or you could be going
to prison.

6
00:00:09.142 --> 00:00:10.912
Where I'm told candy bars
are in short supply.

7
00:00:11.044 --> 00:00:13.515
I can think of something
in even shorter supply.

8
00:00:13.648 --> 00:00:15.148
[♪ playful music plays]

9
00:00:15.282 --> 00:00:17.384
-[Judge Anna] Next witness.
-Lucas is my stepbrother.

10
00:00:17.519 --> 00:00:20.020
and that's the man
who almost killed him.

11
00:00:20.655 --> 00:00:22.456
Mostly just came to see
if we're even now.

12
00:00:22.590 --> 00:00:24.659
What's your obsession with us
getting even? What is it?

13
00:00:24.792 --> 00:00:27.662
We get even too fast.
there won't be any reason
for me to call you anymore.

14
00:00:27.795 --> 00:00:29.697
-[chuckles]
-Is that what you want?

15
00:00:31.131 --> 00:00:32.734
[♪ playful drums play]

16
00:00:42.309 --> 00:00:43.243
[R.J. inhales]

17
00:00:43.377 --> 00:00:45.580
-What?
-What? No. it's good.

18
00:00:45.713 --> 00:00:49.349
It's a-a punctuation thing.
[smacks lips] The. uh.
pop. pop. pop.

19
00:00:49.483 --> 00:00:50.752
It's a lot of them.

20
00:00:50.885 --> 00:00:53.320
The em dashes? Oh. I like them.
They suit the story.

21
00:00:53.453 --> 00:00:57.457
Uh. they're a bit aggressive.
Commas might give you
a better flow.

22
00:00:57.592 --> 00:00:59.694
The story is about
a blind priest who tried
to broker a truce

23
00:00:59.827 --> 00:01:01.563
between MS-13
and the Latin Kings.

24
00:01:01.696 --> 00:01:04.431
I don't need it to flow.
I need it to. like. grab
the reader  and shake them.

25
00:01:04.566 --> 00:01:06.233
-What?
-[chuckles]
You do this every time.

26
00:01:06.366 --> 00:01:09.037
You ask people
to proof your stuff.
and then you argue every point.

27
00:01:09.169 --> 00:01:10.605
-Only the dumb ones.
-[chuckles]

28
00:01:10.738 --> 00:01:12.807
Sofia. liftoff in five minutes.

29
00:01:13.273 --> 00:01:14.909
Oh. Look at you.

30
00:01:15.043 --> 00:01:17.110
earning your keep
proofing my wife's article
so I don't have to.

31
00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:18.445
[R.J.] Mm-hmm.

32
00:01:18.580 --> 00:01:20.147
-She bite your head off yet?
-Pretty much. yeah.

33
00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:21.983
Hey. Mom.
Harper and Violet just texted.

34
00:01:22.115 --> 00:01:25.352
They're going to a kids' spa
on Saturday for mani-pedis
and facials.

35
00:01:25.485 --> 00:01:26.988
and I'm invited.

36
00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:30.090
I'm sorry.
did you say "kids' spa"?
As in. a spa for children?

37
00:01:30.223 --> 00:01:31.826
-Can I go?
-No. you're busy Saturday.

38
00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:33.460
You're volunteering
at the dog rescue.

39
00:01:33.595 --> 00:01:35.597
But can I just skip it
this one time?

40
00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:38.265
You made a commitment.
We keep our commitments
around here.

41
00:01:38.398 --> 00:01:39.466
Go get your bag.

42
00:01:40.434 --> 00:01:42.737
Oh. my goodness.
Take it easy on him. Mwah.

43
00:01:42.870 --> 00:01:45.573
He's got so little going
for him in life.

44
00:01:45.707 --> 00:01:47.274
[phone buzzes]

45
00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:54.147
Uh. dashes or commas.
it's good.

46
00:01:57.986 --> 00:01:59.988
-Hey. how are you?
-[Emi] <i>What are you wearing?</i>

47
00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:01.689
[chuckles] Excuse me?

48
00:02:01.823 --> 00:02:05.225
Don't get excited.
I'm asking because
I may have a job for you.

49
00:02:05.359 --> 00:02:08.328
<i>Change your shirt </i>
<i>and meet me at the address </i>
<i>I'm about to send you.</i>

50
00:02:08.462 --> 00:02:10.230
Why do I have to change
my shirt?

51
00:02:10.364 --> 00:02:12.265
Because these people have money
and refinement.

52
00:02:12.399 --> 00:02:15.168
and the last time they saw
a grown man wearing
an aloha shirt.

53
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:17.170
he was probably cleaning
their pool.

54
00:02:18.773 --> 00:02:20.608
Oh. Okay.

55
00:02:21.743 --> 00:02:23.011
Who needs you to change
your shirt?

56
00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:26.446
Oh. uh. Wish. Yeah. he might
have a new client for me.

57
00:02:26.581 --> 00:02:28.049
Thinks I need to look nice.

58
00:02:28.181 --> 00:02:30.150
Wish. who last time I saw him
was wearing a shirt

59
00:02:30.283 --> 00:02:33.420
with a metal detector
on it and the words
"Beach Better Have My Money"?

60
00:02:33.554 --> 00:02:35.690
[chuckles] Man's got layers.

61
00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:45.700
Hey.

62
00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:47.902
Welcome to the humble abode
of the Carter family.

63
00:02:48.503 --> 00:02:51.139
Carter. Oh. as in Carter Rehab?

64
00:02:51.271 --> 00:02:52.974
-Got it in one.
-Huh.

65
00:02:53.107 --> 00:02:56.878
In addition to owning
the biggest chain of drug
rehab centers in Florida.

66
00:02:57.011 --> 00:03:00.313
Ed Carter also funded
a wing at the Institute
of Contemporary Art.

67
00:03:00.447 --> 00:03:03.518
Gonna go out on a limb
and say he's also one of
your dad's biggest donors.

68
00:03:03.651 --> 00:03:08.056
He is. And so when the family
realized they needed help
with a sensitive issue.

69
00:03:08.188 --> 00:03:09.356
they came to me.

70
00:03:09.489 --> 00:03:10.858
I told them it was a job

71
00:03:10.992 --> 00:03:14.494
for a very dependable. very
discreet private investigator.

72
00:03:14.629 --> 00:03:16.998
-Do good work. Do it quietly.
-Oh. Okay.

73
00:03:17.131 --> 00:03:18.833
I can virtually guarantee
they'll be back for more.

74
00:03:18.966 --> 00:03:20.702
-Okay.
-Background checks.
security gigs.

75
00:03:20.835 --> 00:03:22.570
due diligence.
and they'll pay top dollar.

76
00:03:22.704 --> 00:03:24.672
This shirt.
this is the upgrade?

77
00:03:24.806 --> 00:03:27.340
Let's go hear about
this sensitive issue. shall we?

78
00:03:32.345 --> 00:03:33.748
[person 1] That's Holden.

79
00:03:34.281 --> 00:03:37.350
He lives in Naples
but stays with us whenever
family business requires it.

80
00:03:37.484 --> 00:03:39.754
So. usually. it's just you
and your dad here?

81
00:03:39.887 --> 00:03:41.723
He sends his regards.
by the way.

82
00:03:41.856 --> 00:03:44.792
He's wrapping up some work
in Orlando. but we are both
worried about Holden.

83
00:03:44.926 --> 00:03:48.361
He didn't come home last night.
and he isn't responding
to calls or texts.

84
00:03:48.495 --> 00:03:51.766
You're moving pretty quickly
bringing someone like me on.
Can I ask why?

85
00:03:53.067 --> 00:03:54.769
The more he knows.
the more he can help.

86
00:03:56.070 --> 00:03:58.606
Holden has struggled
with drug addiction for years.

87
00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:00.708
My father and I think
he may have relapsed.

88
00:04:00.842 --> 00:04:03.745
Relapsed. So. he had gotten
clean at some point?

89
00:04:03.878 --> 00:04:05.378
A little over 18 months ago.

90
00:04:05.513 --> 00:04:07.615
He went to a facility
in Switzerland
for the first six months.

91
00:04:07.749 --> 00:04:09.016
then came back to Florida.

92
00:04:09.150 --> 00:04:11.318
Since then. he has been working
as a rehab counselor

93
00:04:11.451 --> 00:04:12.653
in one of our Naples clinics.

94
00:04:13.788 --> 00:04:18.159
It's not like him to be
out of touch. at least
not now that he's sober.

95
00:04:18.291 --> 00:04:21.963
Your job is to find Holden
quickly and quietly.

96
00:04:22.096 --> 00:04:25.465
If he has relapsed.
Mr. Carter doesn't want
the police involved.

97
00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:27.735
Too much chance of the story
breaking to the media.

98
00:04:27.869 --> 00:04:29.269
I understand. and I wanna help.

99
00:04:29.402 --> 00:04:32.607
The best place for me to start
is with whoever saw him last.

100
00:04:32.740 --> 00:04:36.376
I dropped Holden off
at the community center
a little before 1600.

101
00:04:36.511 --> 00:04:37.678
Support group meeting.

102
00:04:37.812 --> 00:04:39.714
So. you knew about
his history with addiction?

103
00:04:39.847 --> 00:04:42.950
Ten years working for
the Carters. They don't keep
any secrets from me.

104
00:04:43.084 --> 00:04:46.453
I drive Holden whenever
he's in town. I waited
up front  like I usually do.

105
00:04:46.587 --> 00:04:48.990
90 mikes later.
everybody comes out
except for Holden.

106
00:04:49.123 --> 00:04:51.659
I went inside.
but no sign of him.

107
00:04:51.793 --> 00:04:53.261
How did he seem to you
yesterday?

108
00:04:53.393 --> 00:04:56.463
Honestly. I was relieved
he wanted to get to a meeting.

109
00:04:56.597 --> 00:04:59.066
He seemed distracted.
a little down.

110
00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:00.868
Any read on
what was bothering him?

111
00:05:01.002 --> 00:05:03.137
He was pretty tight-lipped.
That's part of why
I was worried about him.

112
00:05:03.271 --> 00:05:07.474
You served. huh?
1600. 90 mikes.
You tell time like a soldier.

113
00:05:08.509 --> 00:05:10.845
Not a soldier. A Marine.

114
00:05:10.978 --> 00:05:16.383
Oh. okay. Uh. is that why
Ed Carter chose you
to drive his son?

115
00:05:16.517 --> 00:05:18.586
Wealthy. high-profile family.

116
00:05:18.719 --> 00:05:20.888
Maybe there are security
threats I should know about--

117
00:05:21.022 --> 00:05:22.089
Sorry. no.

118
00:05:22.824 --> 00:05:25.626
The biggest danger to Holden
has always been Holden.

119
00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:26.994
[softly] Got it.

120
00:05:28.361 --> 00:05:31.232
Community center
where  you dropped him off.
can I get the address?

121
00:05:31.364 --> 00:05:33.067
Yeah. yeah. he looks familiar.

122
00:05:33.201 --> 00:05:36.003
He would have come in
around 4:00 p.m. yesterday.
headed for the rec room.

123
00:05:36.137 --> 00:05:39.207
but we think he went out
a different way. maybe
the back  or the side entrance.

124
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:40.641
Out there.
I saw you had cameras--

125
00:05:40.775 --> 00:05:42.643
Hold on. 4:00 p.m.?
In the rec room?

126
00:05:42.777 --> 00:05:45.445
-Yeah. he was here
for an NA meeting.
-Just forget I said I saw him.

127
00:05:45.580 --> 00:05:48.683
And if you're about to ask to
look  at the security footage.
don't even bother.

128
00:05:48.816 --> 00:05:51.384
Anyone our cameras caught
coming in for that meeting

129
00:05:51.519 --> 00:05:53.621
is entitled to their privacy.
okay? End of story.

130
00:05:53.754 --> 00:05:56.858
-I get that.
-My sister is five years
sober.  okay?

131
00:05:56.991 --> 00:05:59.260
Anonymity is crucial
to the work.

132
00:05:59.392 --> 00:06:02.730
I'm here because his sister
thinks he might be
in trouble. Like real trouble.

133
00:06:02.864 --> 00:06:05.533
Look. I get that you don't
want me looking at the footage.

134
00:06:05.666 --> 00:06:08.035
-but you said you were
here yesterday.
-Yeah. so?

135
00:06:08.169 --> 00:06:10.437
So you already saw
everyone that  came in here
for the meeting.

136
00:06:13.541 --> 00:06:14.942
Your guy didn't use
a side exit.

137
00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:17.245
Check the rear door.

138
00:06:22.016 --> 00:06:25.253
Looks like he came out the back
right before the meeting
would've started.

139
00:06:25.385 --> 00:06:28.421
He's making a call.
Now he's talking to someone.

140
00:06:28.556 --> 00:06:29.957
Who? Who's he talking to?

141
00:06:30.091 --> 00:06:32.593
Someone walked up.
I can't see who.
They're off camera.

142
00:06:33.995 --> 00:06:35.663
But your guy.
he looks a little...

143
00:06:36.197 --> 00:06:37.531
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

144
00:06:37.665 --> 00:06:40.001
-What in the world?
-Can I turn around now. please?

145
00:06:40.134 --> 00:06:41.903
Yeah.
I think that would be good.

146
00:06:42.904 --> 00:06:44.605
What the hell is that?

147
00:06:46.774 --> 00:06:50.044
In case you're wondering.
not one of the 12 steps.

148
00:07:04.058 --> 00:07:07.094
-Do you think it's a sex thing?
-Well. this being Florida.

149
00:07:07.228 --> 00:07:09.664
the answer to that question
should almost always
be "maybe."

150
00:07:09.797 --> 00:07:11.966
But no. I-I'm more worried
it could be an abduction.

151
00:07:12.099 --> 00:07:13.433
Abduction?

152
00:07:13.567 --> 00:07:15.603
You see how the big guy keeps
his arm pointed at Holden?

153
00:07:15.736 --> 00:07:17.238
It occurred to me
that wearing that costume

154
00:07:17.371 --> 00:07:18.940
might be a good way
to conceal a gun.

155
00:07:19.073 --> 00:07:20.975
Yeah. well.
you need to be sure.

156
00:07:21.108 --> 00:07:24.845
I'm not about to tell Naomi
maybe her brother was
kidnapped by a furry.

157
00:07:24.979 --> 00:07:26.380
It's a slimy. actually.

158
00:07:26.514 --> 00:07:28.481
I did a little image searching
and realized it's the costume

159
00:07:28.616 --> 00:07:29.951
for Sammy the Sea Cucumber.

160
00:07:30.084 --> 00:07:32.286
-mascot for Rio Vista Prep.
-Huh.

161
00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:34.755
-"Huh." what?
<i>-That's where Holden went </i>
<i>to high school.</i>

162
00:07:34.889 --> 00:07:37.925
Maybe the guy in the costume
was just an old buddy
pulling a prank?

163
00:07:38.059 --> 00:07:39.694
According to the school's
athletic schedule.

164
00:07:39.827 --> 00:07:41.729
Sammy's due to make
an appearance today.

165
00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:44.765
I'll let you know
what he has to say.

166
00:07:44.899 --> 00:07:46.300
[people clamoring]

167
00:07:46.434 --> 00:07:48.302
[shoes squeaking]

168
00:07:50.271 --> 00:07:52.773
-[people cheering]
-[referee blows whistle]

169
00:07:53.908 --> 00:07:55.076
[cheerleaders] Whoo-hoo!

170
00:07:55.209 --> 00:07:56.444
[♪ "Wobble" plays]

171
00:07:58.612 --> 00:08:02.783
Sammy. my name is R.J. Decker.
I'm... a private investigator.

172
00:08:02.917 --> 00:08:05.453
I'd like to ask you
a few questions. if I could.

173
00:08:06.087 --> 00:08:08.589
Sammy. I... All right.

174
00:08:09.323 --> 00:08:12.727
Bit of a time-sensitive issue.
Maybe you can take a break?

175
00:08:13.461 --> 00:08:17.832
Sammy. I have reason to
believe  a man was abducted
at gunpoint last night!

176
00:08:17.965 --> 00:08:20.067
You are my top suspect!

177
00:08:20.201 --> 00:08:21.602
♪ <i>Yeah. yeah</i> ♪

178
00:08:21.736 --> 00:08:24.505
♪ <i>Get in there</i>
<i>Yeah. yeah</i> ♪

179
00:08:24.638 --> 00:08:25.673
[buzzer sounds]

180
00:08:28.776 --> 00:08:32.346
Sorry about before.
I fully commit to Sammy
while I'm in costume.

181
00:08:32.480 --> 00:08:34.849
-You do bring him to life.
-[chuckles]

182
00:08:36.350 --> 00:08:38.686
That isn't me. Sammy worked
a swim meet yesterday.

183
00:08:38.819 --> 00:08:40.388
which means I worked
a swim meet yesterday.

184
00:08:40.521 --> 00:08:43.657
There's no chance
someone could have borrowed
your costume?

185
00:08:43.791 --> 00:08:47.528
Are you kidding?
That costume's
totally different.

186
00:08:48.262 --> 00:08:51.699
[scoffs] No hat.
Look at the Sammy in the video.

187
00:08:53.502 --> 00:08:54.702
[R.J.] Hmm.

188
00:08:54.835 --> 00:08:56.570
-What is that?
Like a sailor's cap?
-Mm-hmm.

189
00:08:56.704 --> 00:08:58.572
That's Sammy. circa 2012.

190
00:08:58.706 --> 00:09:01.475
That costume was retired.
Subsequent Sammys were hatless.

191
00:09:01.609 --> 00:09:04.311
Thank goodness. I don't know
how I'd play with a hat.

192
00:09:04.445 --> 00:09:07.848
Any idea where someone
could have gotten their hands
on the 2012 costume?

193
00:09:07.982 --> 00:09:11.185
Honestly. I assumed
it was destroyed
after the flagpole incident.

194
00:09:11.318 --> 00:09:12.987
Flagpole incident?

195
00:09:13.120 --> 00:09:16.123
Some rich kid hoisted
Sammy up on the flagpole
with the performer inside

196
00:09:16.257 --> 00:09:17.825
and left him there overnight.

197
00:09:17.958 --> 00:09:19.827
[shudders] Costume was soiled
beyond salvage.

198
00:09:20.661 --> 00:09:21.629
Hmm.

199
00:09:21.762 --> 00:09:23.264
-What?
-The guy I'm trying to find.

200
00:09:23.397 --> 00:09:25.599
he went to school here
around that time.

201
00:09:25.733 --> 00:09:27.101
He was definitely a rich kid.

202
00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:30.271
You think that was Sammy 2012
exacting some crazy revenge?

203
00:09:30.404 --> 00:09:32.673
You wouldn't happen to know
that Sammy's real name.
would you?

204
00:09:32.807 --> 00:09:36.010
Ricky Strom. He wore the green
from 2008 to 2012.

205
00:09:36.545 --> 00:09:37.945
[elevator dings]

206
00:09:40.181 --> 00:09:41.550
-Hi!
-[chuckling] What?

207
00:09:41.682 --> 00:09:44.952
-We brought you
an afternoon treat.
-[gasps] You guys!

208
00:09:45.086 --> 00:09:49.023
Mwah. What a nice surprise.
People I arrest.
they never bring me boba.

209
00:09:49.156 --> 00:09:50.591
-Mom. guess what?
-Mmm?

210
00:09:51.158 --> 00:09:53.394
I'm going to the spa with
Harper and Violet after all.

211
00:09:53.528 --> 00:09:56.464
Yeah? We went over this.
You have dog rescue Saturday.

212
00:09:56.597 --> 00:09:58.732
Not anymore.
Catherine fixed it.

213
00:09:59.667 --> 00:10:01.202
-Fixed it?
-I-I called the rescue

214
00:10:01.335 --> 00:10:03.505
and asked if we could shift
Sofia's commitment
to next weekend.

215
00:10:03.637 --> 00:10:05.940
so she'll volunteer two days
instead of just one.

216
00:10:06.073 --> 00:10:08.309
Self-care this weekend.
Dog care next.

217
00:10:08.442 --> 00:10:10.911
That's great. And did Harper
and Violet mention

218
00:10:11.045 --> 00:10:12.880
how much all those spa
treatments are going to cost?

219
00:10:13.013 --> 00:10:14.849
Oh. Catherine took care
of that too.

220
00:10:15.584 --> 00:10:17.952
We talked it all through.
She gets it's a one-time thing.

221
00:10:18.085 --> 00:10:19.353
[Mel] Mm-hmm.

222
00:10:19.487 --> 00:10:21.422
I mean. spa Saturdays will not
become the new norm.

223
00:10:21.556 --> 00:10:24.024
-Mm-mmm.
-Yeah. Mom. Relax.

224
00:10:24.158 --> 00:10:26.093
-Mmm.
-Enjoy your boba.

225
00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:28.762
About that. Uh...

226
00:10:30.397 --> 00:10:32.766
-[sighs] Will this cover
all three?
-Mel.

227
00:10:32.900 --> 00:10:36.571
No. no. no. no. it's only fair.
You get the spa day.
I get the boba.

228
00:10:38.105 --> 00:10:41.208
This was great. Mwah.
But Mommy's  got to get
back to work.

229
00:10:41.909 --> 00:10:44.011
-I'll see you at home.
-See ya.

230
00:10:45.779 --> 00:10:47.848
[♪ "Rio Grande" plays]

231
00:10:52.953 --> 00:10:57.124
Okay. so to be clear. this is
the house of the gentleman

232
00:10:57.258 --> 00:11:01.462
you believe dressed up
as a sea cucumber to kidnap

233
00:11:01.596 --> 00:11:04.198
-his high-school bully
at gunpoint?
-Yeah.

234
00:11:04.798 --> 00:11:07.668
Wow. Florida just keeps
giving and giving.

235
00:11:08.469 --> 00:11:10.104
You see the van
in the driveway?

236
00:11:10.237 --> 00:11:13.073
It's the same one I  saw
Holden Carter get into
at the community center.

237
00:11:13.207 --> 00:11:15.075
You still want me to
just hang back?

238
00:11:15.209 --> 00:11:18.312
Yes. hang back.  You're only
here  to call the cops
if anything goes sideways.

239
00:11:18.445 --> 00:11:21.048
I gotta say.
a violent turn would
almost be worth the headline.

240
00:11:21.182 --> 00:11:23.784
-Hmm?
-"Private eye
and sexy lotto winner

241
00:11:23.918 --> 00:11:26.253
gunned down
by a marine invertebrate."

242
00:11:26.387 --> 00:11:28.689
-[chuckles]
That's straight gold. son.
-[exhales]

243
00:11:35.329 --> 00:11:37.698
[dog barking]

244
00:11:39.833 --> 00:11:40.868
[sighs]

245
00:11:51.245 --> 00:11:52.746
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

246
00:11:59.286 --> 00:12:00.988
[grunts. breathing heavily]

247
00:12:01.889 --> 00:12:03.558
-You're Ricky Strom?
-Yeah.

248
00:12:03.692 --> 00:12:05.627
Does you kicking the door in
count as things going sideways?

249
00:12:05.759 --> 00:12:08.395
'Cause I'm a single digit
from 91...  Whoa.

250
00:12:08.530 --> 00:12:10.931
-I need you to tell me
where Holden is.
-I think someone took him.

251
00:12:11.065 --> 00:12:13.568
Yeah. you did. from the
community center yesterday!

252
00:12:13.702 --> 00:12:15.402
No. No. no. I-I...
Well. yeah. I brought him here.

253
00:12:15.537 --> 00:12:17.838
but then someone else broke in
and did this to me. okay?

254
00:12:17.972 --> 00:12:19.139
They must've kidnapped him.

255
00:12:19.273 --> 00:12:22.443
Wow. "Florida Man abducted
from his own abduction."

256
00:12:22.943 --> 00:12:24.613
It's...
It's another good headline.

257
00:12:35.690 --> 00:12:37.891
I looked everywhere.
No sign of Holden.

258
00:12:38.025 --> 00:12:41.061
I told you whoever broke
in here and attacked me
must have taken him.

259
00:12:41.195 --> 00:12:45.899
Guys. come on.
You think I'm gonna hit myself
in the head? Tie myself up?

260
00:12:46.033 --> 00:12:47.602
Stranger things have happened.
Ricky.

261
00:12:47.736 --> 00:12:51.405
A six-foot cucumber committing
an armed abduction.
for example.

262
00:12:51.539 --> 00:12:55.577
Okay. first. I wasn't armed.
I just pretended to have a gun.

263
00:12:55.710 --> 00:12:59.847
Second. in a certain light.
it wasn't an abduction.

264
00:12:59.980 --> 00:13:02.116
It was more of a...
[inhales] ...prank.

265
00:13:02.249 --> 00:13:05.587
Like flying a guy in a mascot
costume up a flagpole?

266
00:13:07.288 --> 00:13:08.822
You know what Holden did to me?

267
00:13:11.626 --> 00:13:14.161
I was stuck up there all night.

268
00:13:14.629 --> 00:13:18.733
I'd had a lot of water.
Like. a lot of water.

269
00:13:18.866 --> 00:13:21.935
The next morning.
half the school saw me.

270
00:13:22.069 --> 00:13:23.837
humiliated. exhausted...

271
00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:27.509
wet.

272
00:13:27.642 --> 00:13:30.177
It ended my mascot career
because every time I tried

273
00:13:30.311 --> 00:13:33.180
to put on
the costume after that.
I'd have a panic attack.

274
00:13:33.314 --> 00:13:36.483
I'd been offered
a full ride to the University
of Central Florida.

275
00:13:36.618 --> 00:13:38.218
I was gonna take over
as Knightro.

276
00:13:38.352 --> 00:13:40.187
You were gonna wear
the Golden Helmet?

277
00:13:40.321 --> 00:13:44.992
Coming out of UCF.
I could've had my pick:
Mickey. Gritty. Benny the Bull.

278
00:13:45.125 --> 00:13:49.129
A few days ago.
I saw on Holden's social media
that he was in town.

279
00:13:49.263 --> 00:13:51.700
He kept posting
about his sobriety.
how great he was doing.

280
00:13:51.832 --> 00:13:55.869
Yesterday. I just...
I don't know. snapped.

281
00:13:56.837 --> 00:13:58.640
I dug out my Sammy costume.

282
00:13:58.773 --> 00:14:01.108
I waited outside  the Carter
house. and I  tailed them
to the community center.

283
00:14:01.241 --> 00:14:04.078
How did you know he was
gonna come right back out
as soon as he went in?

284
00:14:04.211 --> 00:14:06.013
I didn't. I was just looking
for a place to hide

285
00:14:06.146 --> 00:14:07.881
when I saw him talking
on the phone to someone.

286
00:14:08.015 --> 00:14:09.883
He seemed. I don't know.
nervous.

287
00:14:10.017 --> 00:14:11.586
They were trying to figure out
a place to meet.

288
00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:13.521
I only brought him here
to make him understand

289
00:14:13.655 --> 00:14:15.222
that what he did to me
that night mattered.

290
00:14:15.356 --> 00:14:17.559
But then
the craziest thing happened.

291
00:14:18.560 --> 00:14:20.861
Some mystery man showed up
and ruined all your fun?

292
00:14:20.994 --> 00:14:24.164
No. I'm talking about
before that.

293
00:14:26.500 --> 00:14:27.535
Holden.

294
00:14:28.402 --> 00:14:31.138
he just... listened.

295
00:14:31.271 --> 00:14:35.342
Let me say everything
that I needed to say.
Then he apologized.

296
00:14:35.876 --> 00:14:39.581
And I could tell it wasn't
about me letting him go.
It was about real regret.

297
00:14:39.714 --> 00:14:42.015
He told me about how devoted
he was to his sobriety.

298
00:14:42.149 --> 00:14:44.385
how important making amends is.

299
00:14:44.519 --> 00:14:46.688
And he asked
if I would forgive him.

300
00:14:48.656 --> 00:14:50.023
And I did.

301
00:14:51.425 --> 00:14:54.061
He asked if he could use
my phone. I went
into the kitchen to get it.

302
00:14:54.194 --> 00:14:56.765
And then bam.
I'm hit from behind.
Everything goes black.

303
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:58.600
And I know
that it wasn't Holden

304
00:14:58.733 --> 00:15:00.835
because I was looking right
at him when it happened.

305
00:15:00.968 --> 00:15:04.806
Maybe it was
some friend of Holden's.
Tracked him here. rescued him?

306
00:15:04.938 --> 00:15:07.575
If it was a rescue.
he would have turned up by now.

307
00:15:07.709 --> 00:15:09.076
You said when you walked
up to him

308
00:15:09.209 --> 00:15:11.011
that he was on the phone.
that he seemed nervous.

309
00:15:11.145 --> 00:15:14.248
Oh. you think maybe
he was  talking to the person
who hit me.

310
00:15:15.583 --> 00:15:17.451
Would it help if you had
Holden's phone?

311
00:15:17.585 --> 00:15:20.622
Because I-I-I know where it is.
Or sort of.
I could help you find it.

312
00:15:25.359 --> 00:15:27.494
I was worried that
someone might use
his phone to locate him.

313
00:15:27.629 --> 00:15:29.898
so I told him to toss it
out the van window.

314
00:15:32.166 --> 00:15:34.736
-It's a bag of chips. man.
-You're right.

315
00:15:37.739 --> 00:15:40.307
Are you sure this is
the right stretch of road?

316
00:15:40.441 --> 00:15:44.612
I think so. I was still
in costume. and Sammy's
range of vision is subpar.

317
00:15:45.647 --> 00:15:47.114
Sure.

318
00:15:48.917 --> 00:15:50.951
-Oh! Found it.
-You got it?

319
00:15:51.084 --> 00:15:52.520
-Yeah.
-Okay.

320
00:15:52.654 --> 00:15:54.288
Looks like a lot
of missed calls.

321
00:15:54.421 --> 00:15:58.526
Ten calls from Naomi Carter
and 47 calls from a guy
named Rico Delaware.

322
00:15:58.660 --> 00:16:00.662
Does that name mean
anything to you?

323
00:16:00.795 --> 00:16:04.766
No. I've never heard of him.
But 47 calls. If he was that
desperate to reach Holden...

324
00:16:04.899 --> 00:16:08.770
Yeah. maybe he was
desperate enough to come
and find him last night.

325
00:16:21.114 --> 00:16:23.651
I'm sorry. I know I screwed up.

326
00:16:23.785 --> 00:16:26.654
I shouldn't have made
the spa day happen for Sofia.

327
00:16:26.788 --> 00:16:29.691
[sighs] But she was
so excited.  [chuckles]

328
00:16:29.824 --> 00:16:31.526
And it was easy for you.

329
00:16:31.659 --> 00:16:35.429
$300. $400 for
a couple hours of self-care.
it's no problem. right?

330
00:16:36.296 --> 00:16:37.665
Please don't be this way.

331
00:16:37.799 --> 00:16:40.000
-What way? Poor?
-You are not poor.

332
00:16:40.133 --> 00:16:44.471
No. but I was.
Growing up. my apartment--
two bedrooms. one bathroom--

333
00:16:44.606 --> 00:16:46.139
Six kids. I remember.

334
00:16:46.273 --> 00:16:48.710
Yeah. Can you guess
how many spa days
me and my sisters enjoyed?

335
00:16:49.476 --> 00:16:51.679
You always do this.
You hold the fact

336
00:16:51.813 --> 00:16:53.815
-that I have a little money
against me.
-A little?

337
00:16:53.948 --> 00:16:56.518
My grandparents left me
what they left me. I'm sorry.

338
00:16:56.651 --> 00:17:01.188
Besides. you and I are married.
What's mine is yours.
Yours is mine.

339
00:17:01.856 --> 00:17:04.526
-Like this house?
-Like this house. Our house.

340
00:17:04.659 --> 00:17:06.961
-What?
-You put all the money down.

341
00:17:07.762 --> 00:17:11.533
Yeah. Yeah. I did.
with your permission.

342
00:17:11.666 --> 00:17:14.736
because you agreed
that this was  the best
school district for Sofia

343
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:16.004
by a mile.

344
00:17:16.136 --> 00:17:18.840
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Sorry. I... [stammers]

345
00:17:18.973 --> 00:17:21.308
I love this house. [whispers]
Sofia. she loves this house.

346
00:17:21.441 --> 00:17:22.644
It could just... [inhales]

347
00:17:22.777 --> 00:17:25.412
[smacks lips] It could feel
like something I won

348
00:17:26.079 --> 00:17:27.414
and not something I earned.

349
00:17:29.483 --> 00:17:34.321
The spa day.
I'll sign off on it. okay?
As long as we split it.

350
00:17:34.454 --> 00:17:37.257
Yeah. sure. Whatever you want.

351
00:17:37.391 --> 00:17:38.425
[softly] Okay.

352
00:17:47.367 --> 00:17:48.402
[phone buzzes]

353
00:17:52.072 --> 00:17:54.274
Hey. you get my message about
the mascot and Holden's phone?

354
00:17:54.408 --> 00:17:58.211
<i>-</i> [Emi] <i>I did.</i>
-Guy that called 47 times.
Rico Delaware.

355
00:17:58.345 --> 00:17:59.647
Turns out he's a street artist

356
00:17:59.781 --> 00:18:02.050
who spent some time at one
of the Carter Rehab Clinics.

357
00:18:02.182 --> 00:18:03.685
Apparently. he didn't have
a good experience

358
00:18:03.818 --> 00:18:05.285
because he went to war
with them last year.

359
00:18:05.419 --> 00:18:06.888
He put up a bunch
of anti-Carter graffiti

360
00:18:07.021 --> 00:18:08.255
-all over town.
<i>-R.J.</i>

361
00:18:08.388 --> 00:18:10.058
I mean. 47 calls to a member
of a family you hate.

362
00:18:10.190 --> 00:18:12.660
that's got to be harassment.
maybe even a prelude
to a kidnapping.

363
00:18:12.794 --> 00:18:15.095
We find Rico Delaware.
maybe we find Holden.

364
00:18:15.228 --> 00:18:17.397
R.J.. Holden has been found.

365
00:18:17.532 --> 00:18:19.767
Oh. okay. Where? Where was he?

366
00:18:19.901 --> 00:18:22.570
<i>Some little no-tell motel </i>
<i>downtown.</i>

367
00:18:22.704 --> 00:18:26.440
Housekeeper came in to
clean the room. found him
with a needle in his arm.

368
00:18:27.542 --> 00:18:31.746
He overdosed. I just identified
his body for the Carters.

369
00:18:34.515 --> 00:18:35.583
[sighs]

370
00:18:46.661 --> 00:18:48.428
He's been like that for hours.

371
00:18:48.563 --> 00:18:51.933
When Holden was little.
he was the apple of Dad's eye.

372
00:18:52.066 --> 00:18:54.068
and nothing was too good
for Holden.

373
00:18:54.201 --> 00:18:59.439
So you can imagine how much
it hurt Dad when drugs
came into the picture.

374
00:18:59.574 --> 00:19:02.142
Especially given
the family business. [chuckles]

375
00:19:02.275 --> 00:19:05.613
You could call it ironic.
if all the papers didn't
already do it  years ago.

376
00:19:05.747 --> 00:19:07.682
On the subject of media.

377
00:19:07.815 --> 00:19:11.318
my office has been
in steady contact with
the FLPD regarding messaging.

378
00:19:11.451 --> 00:19:13.988
and we don't see any reasons
for the specifics
of Holden's passing

379
00:19:14.122 --> 00:19:15.523
-to go public.
-Thank you.

380
00:19:15.657 --> 00:19:18.559
And thank you
for trying to help us.

381
00:19:18.693 --> 00:19:21.796
I've already Zelle'd  your
account for your services.
plus a bonus

382
00:19:21.929 --> 00:19:24.364
-for your continued discretion.
-Oh.

383
00:19:24.498 --> 00:19:28.168
Uh. I appreciate that.
But my discretion.
it's-it's part of package.

384
00:19:28.301 --> 00:19:30.705
I'm only sorry
we couldn't find Holden sooner.

385
00:19:33.675 --> 00:19:35.175
Ms. Carter. I'm sorry.
I have to ask.

386
00:19:35.308 --> 00:19:37.812
Did Holden ever mention
anything about
harassing phone calls?

387
00:19:37.945 --> 00:19:39.614
I'm sorry?

388
00:19:39.747 --> 00:19:42.984
When I found his phone.
I saw there was a bunch
of calls from Rico Delaware.

389
00:19:43.117 --> 00:19:44.251
I assume you know that name.

390
00:19:44.384 --> 00:19:47.254
That has to be a mistake.
That man hates my family.

391
00:19:47.387 --> 00:19:49.389
He wouldn't have been
in Holden's phone.

392
00:19:49.524 --> 00:19:52.827
Holden never mention any
business  he needed to tend to

393
00:19:52.960 --> 00:19:54.494
that wasn't related
to the clinics?

394
00:19:54.629 --> 00:19:55.663
Anyone he was planning to meet

395
00:19:55.797 --> 00:19:57.330
-the day he went missing?
-No. no one.

396
00:19:57.464 --> 00:19:58.633
Do you understand any of this?

397
00:19:58.766 --> 00:20:01.002
Naomi. sorry.
Can you excuse us for a moment?

398
00:20:04.038 --> 00:20:05.372
What do you think you're doing?

399
00:20:06.174 --> 00:20:09.309
I think I'm asking questions
about a death I find
a little suspicious.

400
00:20:09.443 --> 00:20:12.345
What's so suspicious about
a drug addict dying
of an overdose?

401
00:20:12.479 --> 00:20:16.216
Ricky Strom described
a guy utterly devoted
to his sobriety.

402
00:20:16.349 --> 00:20:18.251
Then a few hours later.
he's dead of an OD?

403
00:20:18.385 --> 00:20:20.420
I'm sorry. are you talking
about the lunatic

404
00:20:20.555 --> 00:20:22.590
who dressed up
like a vegetable to kidnap him?

405
00:20:22.724 --> 00:20:24.125
There were two kidnappings:

406
00:20:24.257 --> 00:20:25.893
one from the community center.
one from Ricky Strom's house.

407
00:20:26.027 --> 00:20:27.394
-Are you on drugs right now?
-Listen to me.

408
00:20:27.528 --> 00:20:28.996
Something was going on
with Holden that day.

409
00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:31.431
Something completely incidental
to whatever Ricky did.

410
00:20:31.566 --> 00:20:33.735
He clearly had no intention
of going to that support group.

411
00:20:33.868 --> 00:20:35.103
He went in one door.
out the other.

412
00:20:35.235 --> 00:20:36.704
He was on the phone
with somebody outside.

413
00:20:36.838 --> 00:20:39.040
-trying to figure out
a place to meet.
-His dealer. R.J.

414
00:20:39.173 --> 00:20:40.875
He was calling his dealer.

415
00:20:41.008 --> 00:20:43.343
-This is a tragedy. okay?
Not a mystery.
-Can you think of a better way

416
00:20:43.477 --> 00:20:46.080
to murder someone with
a history of drug abuse
than a staged overdose?

417
00:20:46.214 --> 00:20:48.116
-Tell me.
No. I want you to tell me.
-No. No. No more.

418
00:20:48.248 --> 00:20:51.719
These people are
as mortified by Holden's death
as they are devastated.

419
00:20:51.853 --> 00:20:53.521
They want to preserve
his memory.

420
00:20:53.654 --> 00:20:56.356
They want to move on.
You need to let them do both.

421
00:20:56.490 --> 00:21:00.427
Holden's phone-- You said
you found it. Give it to me.
I'll give it to the family.

422
00:21:00.561 --> 00:21:03.631
I don't have it with me.
But I will drop it
by your office later.

423
00:21:26.754 --> 00:21:30.390
Now. retail. brand new.
this beauty will run you 700.

424
00:21:30.525 --> 00:21:34.095
I pulled it out of a dumpster.
Sterilized every part.
Rebuilt the motor.

425
00:21:34.228 --> 00:21:36.097
Now I'm letting it go to you
for 100 bucks.

426
00:21:36.230 --> 00:21:37.999
That's not for everybody.
That's 'cause we're old pals.

427
00:21:38.132 --> 00:21:39.667
Uh-huh.

428
00:21:39.801 --> 00:21:41.035
Oh. hey. speaking of old pals.

429
00:21:41.169 --> 00:21:42.837
-Hey.
-Mauricio.
how are you doing. man?

430
00:21:42.970 --> 00:21:44.471
-Are you kidding me. man?
-[R.J.] Oh.

431
00:21:44.605 --> 00:21:46.808
-[strains. chuckles]
-Come on. Cell block D
forever.  my man.

432
00:21:46.941 --> 00:21:47.942
Saw your van out front.

433
00:21:48.075 --> 00:21:49.342
-Mauricio's Appliance Repair?
-Yeah.

434
00:21:49.476 --> 00:21:50.845
Way to turn your prison hustle
into a real business.

435
00:21:50.978 --> 00:21:52.445
Hey. I can say the same thing
for you.

436
00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:54.649
Well. I-I wasn't a...
wasn't a PI inside.

437
00:21:54.782 --> 00:21:56.449
You sure as hell couldn't mind
your own business.

438
00:21:57.585 --> 00:21:59.821
Reason I called.
I was hoping you could
unlock this for me.

439
00:21:59.954 --> 00:22:01.856
Yeah. It's yours. right?

440
00:22:01.989 --> 00:22:03.624
Well. if it were mine.
I would know the password.

441
00:22:03.758 --> 00:22:06.294
Untrue. People forget
their passwords all the time.

442
00:22:06.426 --> 00:22:10.665
And unlocking someone's phone
without his or her explicit
permission is illegal.

443
00:22:10.798 --> 00:22:12.934
It's yours. right?

444
00:22:13.768 --> 00:22:15.536
Oh. yeah. it's mine.
100% mine. All mine.

445
00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:18.371
-Great. Give me a day.
-Beautiful. Thank you.

446
00:22:19.339 --> 00:22:22.810
Now look. Wish. I could let
the blender go for 90.  but
after that I'm giving it away.

447
00:22:26.881 --> 00:22:29.784
Oh. move fast and tight
to the wall for outlines.

448
00:22:30.318 --> 00:22:31.418
-Rico Delaware?
-Yeah.

449
00:22:31.552 --> 00:22:33.420
Or should I call you
Professor Delaware?

450
00:22:33.554 --> 00:22:35.556
I know the university made you
an artist in residence.

451
00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:39.660
Selfies gotta wait
till after class. okay?
I don't like to break flow.

452
00:22:39.794 --> 00:22:42.697
I respect flow. But. uh.
I'm a private investigator.

453
00:22:42.830 --> 00:22:44.198
I'd like to ask you
a few  questions

454
00:22:44.332 --> 00:22:46.000
about your relationship
with Holden Carter.

455
00:22:46.133 --> 00:22:48.468
What's a PI care about
me and him?

456
00:22:48.603 --> 00:22:52.073
A lot. actually. Mostly because
he was found dead last night.

457
00:22:57.178 --> 00:23:01.883
People like me...
People like Holden... [inhales]

458
00:23:02.016 --> 00:23:05.686
The number of times that we
stick a needle in our arm
and never wake up...

459
00:23:07.121 --> 00:23:09.456
Uh. you'd think I'd be used
to it by now. but no.

460
00:23:09.590 --> 00:23:11.058
It messes me up every time.

461
00:23:13.327 --> 00:23:14.996
The reason why I wanted
to talk to you. Rico.

462
00:23:15.129 --> 00:23:17.932
I'm not sure Holden put
that needle in his arm himself.

463
00:23:18.966 --> 00:23:20.101
You think someone killed him?

464
00:23:22.003 --> 00:23:23.571
You think I killed him?

465
00:23:23.704 --> 00:23:26.073
Well. it's no secret
you had a grudge
against the Carter family.

466
00:23:26.207 --> 00:23:28.876
My grudge is with Ed Carter.
the way he runs his business.

467
00:23:29.010 --> 00:23:31.012
Me and Holden. we were cool.

468
00:23:33.047 --> 00:23:35.716
A while back.
Holden reached out to me.

469
00:23:35.850 --> 00:23:40.955
He wanted to meet to talk about
my experience with
Carter Rehab.

470
00:23:42.290 --> 00:23:44.125
I obliged.

471
00:23:44.258 --> 00:23:48.529
Told him about recruiters
pulling 5K a head for addicts
with primo insurance.

472
00:23:48.663 --> 00:23:51.399
About how the facilities
are straight-up turnstiles.

473
00:23:51.532 --> 00:23:54.168
How no one gives a crap
if you get sober.

474
00:23:54.302 --> 00:23:56.304
just so long
as the insurance keeps paying.

475
00:23:58.940 --> 00:24:02.576
This one guy I knew. he went
through four rounds of that.

476
00:24:02.710 --> 00:24:05.746
The fourth time. he OD'd
right there in the clinic.

477
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:07.815
You ever tried talking
to the cops?

478
00:24:07.949 --> 00:24:11.619
Oh. yeah. You tell me when
police start listening to
junkies. former or otherwise.

479
00:24:11.752 --> 00:24:14.855
And Holden? How did he take
everything you told him?

480
00:24:14.989 --> 00:24:18.392
He was upset. you know.
but he said that he'd take it
all to his old man.

481
00:24:18.526 --> 00:24:21.262
-How did that conversation go?
-I don't know. all right?

482
00:24:21.395 --> 00:24:23.496
I figured I said my piece.
I gave him some space.

483
00:24:23.631 --> 00:24:26.167
Well. I happen to know
you called him 47 times
the other night.

484
00:24:26.300 --> 00:24:27.635
How's that giving him space?

485
00:24:27.768 --> 00:24:30.438
Me and Holden. well.
we stayed in contact.

486
00:24:30.571 --> 00:24:34.342
He wanted me to stay clean.
I wanted him to stay clean.

487
00:24:35.109 --> 00:24:37.511
The other. night all I could
think about was getting high.

488
00:24:37.645 --> 00:24:39.146
So you called Holden?

489
00:24:39.280 --> 00:24:41.983
Yeah. When I couldn't  reach
him. I freaked. I kept calling.

490
00:24:43.250 --> 00:24:44.952
But then I said to myself.

491
00:24:45.086 --> 00:24:47.722
"You know what he would say?
Get your ass to a meeting."
And so I did.

492
00:24:47.855 --> 00:24:51.491
My sister drove me there
and back.

493
00:24:51.993 --> 00:24:54.462
This is her number
if you wanna call her.

494
00:24:54.595 --> 00:24:56.364
Please. it's okay. It's okay.

495
00:24:57.031 --> 00:25:01.202
Look. as far as I've been able
to tell. Holden seemed like
he was in a good place.

496
00:25:01.335 --> 00:25:03.204
But I don't know.
What do you think?

497
00:25:04.405 --> 00:25:08.042
Every addict is just one
bad day away from a slip.

498
00:25:09.977 --> 00:25:14.181
But if you're right.
if someone did this to him.

499
00:25:15.182 --> 00:25:16.751
then you need to catch him.

500
00:25:17.852 --> 00:25:19.320
Because trust me.

501
00:25:20.554 --> 00:25:23.324
that is the last way
he would have wanted to go.

502
00:25:37.204 --> 00:25:38.572
[person] R.J. Decker?

503
00:25:38.706 --> 00:25:40.107
-Yeah.
-[door closes]

504
00:25:40.241 --> 00:25:43.944
Agent Jacob Koop. IRS.
Criminal Investigation
Division.

505
00:25:44.078 --> 00:25:47.948
Wow. I knew I shouldn't have
rounded up my mileage
on that last tax return.

506
00:25:48.082 --> 00:25:50.051
[chuckles] Actually.
I wanna talk to you

507
00:25:50.184 --> 00:25:53.054
about the work you've
been doing for the. uh.
Carter family.

508
00:25:53.187 --> 00:25:56.857
Well. if you know the kind
of work I do. you know
I can't talk about my clients.

509
00:25:56.991 --> 00:26:00.529
I can't even confirm the people
you're talking about
are my clients.

510
00:26:00.661 --> 00:26:02.430
I'll just cut to the chase
then.

511
00:26:02.563 --> 00:26:05.900
See. I'm here because
I don't think Holden Carter's
overdose was an accident.

512
00:26:07.001 --> 00:26:10.171
I think someone
forced him to shoot up.
probably at gunpoint.

513
00:26:10.304 --> 00:26:14.742
[breathes deeply]
Well. I don't think I'll be
violating confidentiality

514
00:26:14.875 --> 00:26:16.277
to tell you I've been thinking
the same thing.

515
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:17.912
-Oh. good.
-Do you wanna come inside?

516
00:26:18.045 --> 00:26:19.514
You wanna compare notes?

517
00:26:19.647 --> 00:26:22.116
You know. I'd love to talk
but not here.
Someplace public.

518
00:26:22.249 --> 00:26:24.685
-All right.
you know FM Station?
-I'll find it.

519
00:26:25.219 --> 00:26:28.255
Why do we have to go
somewhere public to talk
about Holden Carter?

520
00:26:29.356 --> 00:26:31.826
Well. because I think
you're the one that killed him.

521
00:26:37.231 --> 00:26:39.133
Crazy day.
You accuse a guy of murder.

522
00:26:39.266 --> 00:26:41.735
he ends up introducing you
to the best burger you've had
in years.

523
00:26:41.869 --> 00:26:43.538
Not that it's alleviating
any suspicion.

524
00:26:43.671 --> 00:26:46.674
Yeah. I get it. Ex-con takes
money from a shady family.

525
00:26:46.807 --> 00:26:49.343
Twenty-four hours later.
that family's black sheep
winds up dead.

526
00:26:49.477 --> 00:26:51.312
I'd take a look at me too.

527
00:26:51.445 --> 00:26:54.782
Coroner's report says Holden
died between 7:00
and 9:00 p.m.  two nights ago.

528
00:26:54.915 --> 00:26:57.651
-Can you account
for your whereabouts?
-Oh. I can.

529
00:26:57.785 --> 00:27:00.387
But first I'd like to confirm
a few of my suspicions.

530
00:27:00.522 --> 00:27:03.257
[inhales] Naomi Carter paid me
electronically this morning.

531
00:27:03.390 --> 00:27:04.925
By the afternoon.
I'm getting a visit from you.

532
00:27:05.059 --> 00:27:07.628
Which tells me
the IRS is monitoring
the family's accounts.

533
00:27:07.761 --> 00:27:11.365
And since you work in
criminal investigations.
ain't your standard audit.

534
00:27:12.366 --> 00:27:13.934
You've been looking into
something bigger.

535
00:27:14.068 --> 00:27:16.437
Something that now
includes Holden's death.

536
00:27:17.071 --> 00:27:19.039
Well. I can neither
confirm nor deny...

537
00:27:20.107 --> 00:27:23.344
is something we're required
to say when someone's
got us dead to rights.

538
00:27:24.211 --> 00:27:27.148
Holden was looking into
some pretty dark corners
of the family business.

539
00:27:27.281 --> 00:27:28.916
I think he was gonna have
a talk with his dad.

540
00:27:29.049 --> 00:27:30.484
I think he did.
but it went poorly.

541
00:27:30.619 --> 00:27:32.987
So poorly. in fact.
his next step is
reaching out to the IRS.

542
00:27:33.120 --> 00:27:35.322
Which makes me wonder
if it was you he was planning
on meeting

543
00:27:35.456 --> 00:27:37.858
when he snuck out
of a support group meeting
the other day.

544
00:27:39.193 --> 00:27:40.895
Well. I can neither confirm
nor deny.

545
00:27:41.028 --> 00:27:43.964
Then don't confirm
or deny this either:
Holden was gonna whistleblow.

546
00:27:44.098 --> 00:27:45.699
He was gonna take down
Carter Rehab

547
00:27:45.833 --> 00:27:48.302
because unlike his dad.
he actually cares about
addicts getting better.

548
00:27:48.435 --> 00:27:51.405
[inhales] Those whereabouts
you were gonna account for?

549
00:27:51.540 --> 00:27:54.175
Phone. computer records prove
I was home all night. What?

550
00:27:54.308 --> 00:27:56.110
It's gonna take me days
to subpoena those records.

551
00:27:56.243 --> 00:27:58.145
Okay. That's good. It'll give
us both more time to prove

552
00:27:58.279 --> 00:28:00.047
his dad was behind
what happened to him.

553
00:28:01.015 --> 00:28:04.351
The premise that you killed
Holden but might be willing
to roll on his dad

554
00:28:04.485 --> 00:28:07.656
was all I had left.
and if that premise is wrong.
then I have nothing.

555
00:28:07.821 --> 00:28:11.192
And if I have nothing.
trust me. you've got
less than nothing.

556
00:28:11.325 --> 00:28:12.561
[R.J. sighs]

557
00:28:12.693 --> 00:28:14.828
Ed Carter's gonna get away
with everything.

558
00:28:16.964 --> 00:28:18.399
[♪ "Dancing Mood" playing]

559
00:28:19.733 --> 00:28:21.835
-Someone had a crappy day.
-[sighs]

560
00:28:22.336 --> 00:28:23.672
Yeah. someone did.

561
00:28:23.804 --> 00:28:25.674
You wanna join me for a beer?

562
00:28:26.541 --> 00:28:27.576
Yes. I do.

563
00:28:30.612 --> 00:28:31.646
[Catherine clears throat]

564
00:28:34.181 --> 00:28:35.783
[breathes deeply] Thank you.

565
00:28:36.917 --> 00:28:39.787
Let me guess:
Wish still unhappy
about the way you're dressing?

566
00:28:39.920 --> 00:28:41.322
Mm-hmm.

567
00:28:41.455 --> 00:28:43.592
He's the one who brought you
the new client. right?

568
00:28:43.724 --> 00:28:47.061
Mm-hmm. Judging by that second
beer you had lined up.

569
00:28:47.194 --> 00:28:49.096
I'm guessing you had
a crappy day too?

570
00:28:50.397 --> 00:28:52.266
Mel and I had
the money fight again.

571
00:28:53.067 --> 00:28:54.569
Oof.

572
00:28:54.703 --> 00:28:57.271
Yeah. oof. I know.
I pay for stuff
when I can pay for stuff.

573
00:28:57.404 --> 00:29:00.074
and she acts like
I'm some eccentric millionaire.

574
00:29:00.908 --> 00:29:04.679
Back when you and I were
together.  I paid more rent.
I paid for more meals out.

575
00:29:04.812 --> 00:29:06.280
You were always okay with it.

576
00:29:10.217 --> 00:29:12.119
Wait. You weren't okay with it?

577
00:29:12.253 --> 00:29:14.755
[sighs] I mean. it's not
like I wasn't okay with it.

578
00:29:14.888 --> 00:29:17.057
It just took me
a little while to get used to.

579
00:29:17.191 --> 00:29:20.027
I like to pay my own way.
Mel does too.

580
00:29:20.160 --> 00:29:21.596
What?

581
00:29:21.730 --> 00:29:24.331
Nothing. I just found out that
I'm repeating an ugly pattern

582
00:29:24.465 --> 00:29:27.901
from my first failed marriage.
No biggie.

583
00:29:28.035 --> 00:29:29.738
No. you're not repeating
anything.

584
00:29:29.870 --> 00:29:33.274
Unlike me. Mel said something.
That's not repetition.
that's progress.

585
00:29:33.907 --> 00:29:36.243
[sighs] But what do I do?

586
00:29:36.377 --> 00:29:39.480
Get in there.
If she said something.
you say something back.

587
00:29:39.614 --> 00:29:40.749
[phone buzzes]

588
00:29:45.052 --> 00:29:47.921
-What?
-My crappy day.
it ain't over yet.

589
00:29:50.625 --> 00:29:52.359
Hey. What happened?

590
00:29:52.493 --> 00:29:56.497
I was loading groceries
in the van. and some huge guy
comes out of nowhere.

591
00:29:56.631 --> 00:29:59.768
coldcocks me and snatches
the phone you gave me
and ran off.

592
00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:01.402
-He only took the phone?
-Yeah.

593
00:30:01.536 --> 00:30:03.738
The three of us are the only
ones that knew Mauricio had it.

594
00:30:03.871 --> 00:30:06.641
So. how would anyone know
to track him down?

595
00:30:06.775 --> 00:30:10.210
Wish. have you ever heard
of Find My Phone?

596
00:30:10.344 --> 00:30:13.548
It enables users
to find their phones.

597
00:30:13.682 --> 00:30:16.584
-Yeah. but the owner's dead.
-I'm so-- He's what?

598
00:30:16.718 --> 00:30:20.689
-Did you get a look at him?
-Not really. I mean.
he was white. jacked.

599
00:30:20.854 --> 00:30:23.625
Kind of like that Aryan Nation
guy who was weirdly good
at kickball.

600
00:30:23.758 --> 00:30:25.192
-You remember him?
-Oh. yeah.

601
00:30:25.326 --> 00:30:28.697
-Oh. That-That's not good.
-What?

602
00:30:28.829 --> 00:30:31.365
You got a-a dent in your face.
Hold on.

603
00:30:32.399 --> 00:30:35.637
Looks like a little lollipop
with wings.

604
00:30:38.238 --> 00:30:41.141
That ain't a lollipop.
It's a globe
from a signet ring.

605
00:30:41.275 --> 00:30:42.744
You got punched in the face
by a Marine.

606
00:30:42.876 --> 00:30:44.311
You know who he is?

607
00:30:44.445 --> 00:30:45.946
Yeah. I do. [sighs]

608
00:30:46.080 --> 00:30:48.650
I'm starting to think
he's the one that killed
Holden Carter.

609
00:30:57.991 --> 00:31:00.729
-[door opens]
-[suspect] Are the cuffs
really necessary?

610
00:31:00.861 --> 00:31:03.798
-[door closes]
-You're a suspect
in a violent robbery.

611
00:31:03.931 --> 00:31:06.300
Did the officers
who pulled you over
fail to make that clear?

612
00:31:06.433 --> 00:31:09.704
They did.
And then I made it clear
that they had the wrong guy.

613
00:31:09.838 --> 00:31:14.341
And yet they found this.
Property reported stolen
by the victim in your car.

614
00:31:14.475 --> 00:31:18.847
It belonged to the late
Holden Carter. son of
your employer. Ed Carter. yes?

615
00:31:18.979 --> 00:31:20.447
[phone buzzes]

616
00:31:20.582 --> 00:31:22.182
I'm thinking
you were able to track it
to the man you assaulted

617
00:31:22.316 --> 00:31:25.754
because you or Ed or one
of his other flunkies
at Carter Rehab

618
00:31:25.886 --> 00:31:29.022
put spyware on the phone
that lets you see Holden's
movements.

619
00:31:29.156 --> 00:31:31.125
maybe even read
his emails and texts.

620
00:31:31.258 --> 00:31:32.861
-This is insane.
-[phone buzzes]

621
00:31:32.993 --> 00:31:35.429
I found that phone
under a car seat today.

622
00:31:35.563 --> 00:31:39.032
Obviously.
Holden left it there. I didn't
beat anyone up to get it.

623
00:31:41.268 --> 00:31:43.070
Take a look at these.

624
00:31:43.203 --> 00:31:46.641
And then take a look
at that ring of yours.

625
00:31:46.775 --> 00:31:47.876
[suspect chuckles]

626
00:31:49.143 --> 00:31:52.747
Sorry. This guy must have
pissed off a different Marine.

627
00:31:52.881 --> 00:31:55.517
How did Ed take it
when he heard Holden
slipped away the other night?

628
00:31:55.650 --> 00:31:58.853
Did he already know Holden
had a meeting with the IRS?

629
00:31:59.888 --> 00:32:03.090
I'm just a driver.
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

630
00:32:03.223 --> 00:32:05.959
Mmm. You could tell
from the spyware on the phone

631
00:32:06.093 --> 00:32:09.697
that Holden exited
the community center
as soon as he entered it.

632
00:32:09.831 --> 00:32:11.098
I'm guessing you got
to the parking lot

633
00:32:11.231 --> 00:32:15.068
just as he got into a van
with a man named Ricky Strom.

634
00:32:15.202 --> 00:32:19.006
You followed them
to Mr. Strom's house.
and then you called Daddy.

635
00:32:19.139 --> 00:32:22.744
He got nervous. Thought maybe
this was Holden's IRS contact.

636
00:32:22.877 --> 00:32:25.647
So he told you it was time.
Holden had to go.

637
00:32:25.780 --> 00:32:30.184
Give up your boss.
Confess to staging Holden's OD.

638
00:32:30.317 --> 00:32:33.420
Maybe the State of Florida
won't put a needle in your arm.

639
00:32:34.756 --> 00:32:38.292
Go ahead.
Charge me with this assault
if you think it'll stick.

640
00:32:38.425 --> 00:32:41.495
But if you want to talk
to me again.
I'll come back with a lawyer.

641
00:32:42.362 --> 00:32:45.800
Mr. Carter will hire the best
that money can buy.

642
00:32:49.671 --> 00:32:51.371
[elevator bell dings]

643
00:32:59.614 --> 00:33:01.683
Did the best I could.

644
00:33:01.816 --> 00:33:04.552
Only thing
that guy said in there
that was even remotely true

645
00:33:04.686 --> 00:33:07.020
is Ed Carter's loaded.
which is funny.

646
00:33:07.154 --> 00:33:10.357
His daughter hiring a PI
who works out of a pool house

647
00:33:10.491 --> 00:33:13.494
instead of some big.
white-glove security firm.

648
00:33:13.628 --> 00:33:15.897
Yeah. I don't know. Must have
liked my website. I guess.

649
00:33:18.999 --> 00:33:20.535
[phone buzzes]

650
00:33:25.472 --> 00:33:27.675
-[phone chimes]
-[R.J. sighs]

651
00:33:29.409 --> 00:33:30.477
Great.

652
00:33:39.654 --> 00:33:41.054
What. too loud inside?

653
00:33:41.188 --> 00:33:43.323
For this conversation? Yes.
because I need you to hear me.

654
00:33:43.457 --> 00:33:45.693
I tried to do you a favor
when I brought you to Naomi.

655
00:33:45.827 --> 00:33:48.596
Now her father is threatening
to cut off ties with mine.

656
00:33:48.730 --> 00:33:50.430
That'd be bad. right?

657
00:33:50.565 --> 00:33:53.033
Losing all that money
Ed Carter's making
not keeping addicts off drugs.

658
00:33:53.166 --> 00:33:54.368
What are you talking about?

659
00:33:54.501 --> 00:33:56.136
Carter Rehab doesn't want
people getting better.

660
00:33:56.270 --> 00:33:59.507
It's bad for business.
Holden was about to blow
the whistle.

661
00:33:59.641 --> 00:34:01.676
If we open up the phone.
there's gonna be spyware on it

662
00:34:01.809 --> 00:34:03.912
that'll prove his dad knew
he was talking to the IRS.

663
00:34:04.044 --> 00:34:07.447
Hold on. If we open his phone?
You mean you don't know
there's spyware?

664
00:34:07.582 --> 00:34:10.317
The phone's locked.
Can you think of another reason

665
00:34:10.450 --> 00:34:12.720
why Ed sent his hatchet man to
get it back yesterday? Tell me.

666
00:34:12.854 --> 00:34:15.957
Wow. I can't believe this.
I can't believe
you accused Ed Carter

667
00:34:16.089 --> 00:34:19.226
of having his own son killed
without any proof.

668
00:34:19.359 --> 00:34:21.061
'Cause if there's no proof.
there's no crime. right?

669
00:34:21.194 --> 00:34:24.799
Isn't that
the Ochoa family motto?
Look. Holden is dead.

670
00:34:24.933 --> 00:34:27.735
A guy that died trying
to be a better man. to fight
for people who needed help.

671
00:34:27.869 --> 00:34:30.203
He was willing to go up
against his own father.

672
00:34:30.337 --> 00:34:33.041
Not because it was easy.
'Cause  it was the right thing
to do.

673
00:34:33.173 --> 00:34:35.877
Of course. you wouldn't care
about a guy like that.

674
00:34:36.010 --> 00:34:38.178
Next time you wanna do me
a favor. don't do it.

675
00:34:38.312 --> 00:34:40.080
I don't need business
like yours.

676
00:34:48.623 --> 00:34:52.727
I have to admit I was surprised
to hear from you this morning.

677
00:34:52.860 --> 00:34:54.161
I was pretty clear
with your father.

678
00:34:54.294 --> 00:34:57.331
I thought our families
needed some time apart.

679
00:34:57.464 --> 00:35:01.970
You were. But he and I
both felt we'd be remiss

680
00:35:02.102 --> 00:35:06.774
if we didn't at least try
to apologize for Mr. Decker's
actions yesterday.

681
00:35:06.908 --> 00:35:09.544
Next time. we'll do a better
job vetting our referrals.

682
00:35:09.677 --> 00:35:11.445
You're assuming
there'll be a next time.

683
00:35:11.579 --> 00:35:14.549
I'm well aware we need
to earn back your trust.

684
00:35:15.683 --> 00:35:17.652
That's why
I-I brought you this.

685
00:35:19.754 --> 00:35:23.825
Holden's phone.
My office was able
to get it back from the police.

686
00:35:23.958 --> 00:35:26.828
It wasn't too difficult.
considering there was no crime

687
00:35:26.961 --> 00:35:28.295
they could actually
connect it to. but...

688
00:35:28.428 --> 00:35:30.832
And given the scrutiny
Mr. Decker was inviting.

689
00:35:30.965 --> 00:35:32.967
I thought you would value
having it back.

690
00:35:40.440 --> 00:35:41.843
If there's nothing else...

691
00:35:44.746 --> 00:35:45.780
[Emi sighs]

692
00:35:47.081 --> 00:35:50.551
Yeah. actually.
there is one more thing.
It was locked when we got it.

693
00:35:50.685 --> 00:35:53.121
My father and I didn't want to
assume you'd know the password.

694
00:35:53.253 --> 00:35:56.356
So we did you the favor
of bringing it to one of
our communications experts.

695
00:35:56.490 --> 00:36:00.528
The intention was to give you
access to Holden's photo album.

696
00:36:00.662 --> 00:36:02.530
All those precious memories.

697
00:36:03.765 --> 00:36:05.867
But then our expert found
something else.

698
00:36:06.466 --> 00:36:11.438
Someone was tracking
Holden's movements and reading
his emails and text messages.

699
00:36:12.006 --> 00:36:15.677
Whoever it was. they knew
he was looking to go public

700
00:36:15.810 --> 00:36:19.446
with some very serious concerns
about treatment practices
at Carter Rehab.

701
00:36:19.580 --> 00:36:23.350
If you're suggesting
I had  anything to do with
what happened to Holden--

702
00:36:23.483 --> 00:36:25.586
I'm not suggesting anything.

703
00:36:26.888 --> 00:36:31.592
I'm just hoping
my family ends up back
in your family's good graces.

704
00:36:33.895 --> 00:36:35.730
Because a man who would
have his own son killed

705
00:36:35.863 --> 00:36:38.032
can never have
too many friends.  can he?

706
00:36:42.036 --> 00:36:46.140
Tell your father when the time
comes. he'll have my support.

707
00:36:51.679 --> 00:36:54.549
It's important to me that
he knows. that you both know.

708
00:36:54.682 --> 00:36:59.419
Holden wasn't supposed to die.
The plan was only to
discredit him.

709
00:36:59.554 --> 00:37:03.624
To make it so the feds
couldn't take him seriously
as a witness.

710
00:37:03.758 --> 00:37:05.358
So all you really wanted to do

711
00:37:05.492 --> 00:37:08.029
was throw away all the hard
work he did to get sober.

712
00:37:08.162 --> 00:37:11.933
It was a mistake.
A terrible mistake.

713
00:37:13.500 --> 00:37:17.004
Naomi. Can I assume
she played no part in this?

714
00:37:17.138 --> 00:37:21.876
Of course not.
She loved her brother.
I loved Holden too.

715
00:37:22.009 --> 00:37:24.377
I loved him as much
as your father loves you.

716
00:37:26.881 --> 00:37:28.248
I'm sure that's true.

717
00:37:40.228 --> 00:37:41.261
How'd it go?

718
00:37:43.497 --> 00:37:46.601
[Ed Carter] <i>It's important </i>
<i>to me that he knows. </i>
<i>that you both know.</i>

719
00:37:46.734 --> 00:37:50.938
<i>Holden wasn't supposed to die.</i>
<i>The plan was only to </i>
<i>discredit him.</i>

720
00:37:51.072 --> 00:37:55.109
<i>To make it so the feds </i>
<i>couldn't take him seriously </i>
<i>as a witness.</i>

721
00:37:55.977 --> 00:37:57.178
Who gets this first?

722
00:37:58.478 --> 00:38:01.783
My new friend at the IRS.
I'll go see him
after I drive you home.

723
00:38:02.884 --> 00:38:06.353
Actually. I'll come with you.
And then I need a drink.

724
00:38:07.955 --> 00:38:09.624
[♪ "Alvarado" plays]

725
00:38:22.236 --> 00:38:24.505
Uh. I didn't do all this.

726
00:38:24.639 --> 00:38:25.940
[Catherine] You're early.

727
00:38:26.607 --> 00:38:30.178
Uh. Mel. this is Francis.
She writes the <i>Herald</i> 's
financial advice column.

728
00:38:30.310 --> 00:38:32.680
Oh. okay. Hi. Nice to meet you.

729
00:38:34.782 --> 00:38:37.317
Uh. I-I. uh. was just leaving.

730
00:38:39.520 --> 00:38:40.955
You have a lovely home.

731
00:38:42.890 --> 00:38:44.091
Thanks again. Francis.

732
00:38:47.895 --> 00:38:50.264
Is it terrible I'm relieved
you weren't about to pitch
a threesome?

733
00:38:50.397 --> 00:38:53.668
[chuckles] A little.
but whatever.

734
00:38:53.801 --> 00:38:56.037
Just come sit. [chuckles]

735
00:38:57.171 --> 00:38:59.974
The real reason
I had Francis come over

736
00:39:00.107 --> 00:39:02.475
-was to...
-Mm-hmm.

737
00:39:02.610 --> 00:39:06.479
...help me prepare
a trip for you

738
00:39:06.614 --> 00:39:09.584
into the future. or at least
our financial future.

739
00:39:09.717 --> 00:39:11.418
[♪ "One More Change" plays]

740
00:39:12.887 --> 00:39:16.423
This line represents. based
on all sorts of variables.

741
00:39:16.557 --> 00:39:19.827
that were frankly
a little over my head.
my future income.

742
00:39:19.961 --> 00:39:23.865
[smacks lips]
And this one predicts yours.

743
00:39:25.566 --> 00:39:29.670
And what I'm looking at
should make me as happy
as you are because...

744
00:39:29.804 --> 00:39:33.941
Because between your gradual-
if-inexorable ascension
through the ranks of the FLPD

745
00:39:34.075 --> 00:39:36.544
and the long. sad death march
that is print media.

746
00:39:36.677 --> 00:39:41.215
Francis has you passing me
in annual take-home pay
no later than 2032.

747
00:39:41.349 --> 00:39:44.986
By 2042... Actually. you know.
don't even look at 2042.

748
00:39:45.119 --> 00:39:47.221
-The point is...
-Mmm?

749
00:39:48.122 --> 00:39:50.191
...it's gonna be
a long marriage.

750
00:39:50.324 --> 00:39:52.994
And our love will be
a constant. but our money...

751
00:39:53.527 --> 00:39:55.563
Now. that's gonna be
variable as hell.

752
00:39:55.696 --> 00:40:00.268
So will you.
every once in a while.
let me be a little generous

753
00:40:00.400 --> 00:40:04.872
if I promise to be
a financial drain on you
in the years to come?

754
00:40:05.006 --> 00:40:10.410
I'll do my best.
and I look forward
to carrying your broke ass.

755
00:40:10.544 --> 00:40:12.013
[Catherine chuckles]

756
00:40:12.513 --> 00:40:15.448
2042. That's dark.

757
00:40:19.854 --> 00:40:21.255
[Mel moans]

758
00:40:21.989 --> 00:40:23.524
-Gross.
-[Mel] Mmm.

759
00:40:25.159 --> 00:40:26.260
Hola to you too. <i>mija</i> .

760
00:40:26.394 --> 00:40:28.629
I'm hungry.
Is there a dinner planned?

761
00:40:28.763 --> 00:40:29.797
Uh...

762
00:40:32.767 --> 00:40:36.137
Takeout? Someplace cheap?

763
00:40:37.371 --> 00:40:38.673
Someplace cheap.

764
00:40:38.806 --> 00:40:42.944
♪ <i>This heavy load </i>
<i>Helped me set it down</i> ♪

765
00:40:43.077 --> 00:40:44.745
[Emi] Of course. I understand.

766
00:40:45.579 --> 00:40:49.583
Well. I'm here for you
no matter what.

767
00:40:50.418 --> 00:40:52.386
Okay. Bye.

768
00:40:53.554 --> 00:40:54.722
That was Naomi?

769
00:40:54.855 --> 00:40:56.857
-Yeah.
-How is she holding up?

770
00:40:56.991 --> 00:41:01.662
Mmm. About as well
as you'd expect. But she is
grateful for what you did.

771
00:41:01.796 --> 00:41:03.496
[R.J. chuckles]

772
00:41:03.631 --> 00:41:06.200
And she's planning
to work with the IRS
as they investigate everything

773
00:41:06.334 --> 00:41:10.538
and then start instituting
the changes Holden wanted
at the clinics.

774
00:41:10.671 --> 00:41:11.706
Good.

775
00:41:13.473 --> 00:41:16.177
-To Holden?
-To Holden.

776
00:41:19.113 --> 00:41:21.315
Listen. some of
the things I said yesterday.

777
00:41:21.449 --> 00:41:25.086
I-I didn't like saying 'em.
but I'm glad they got through.

778
00:41:25.553 --> 00:41:30.024
Hold up. [chuckles]
You think I did what I did
because of you?

779
00:41:30.157 --> 00:41:33.493
Did somebody else accuse you
of choosing your dad's
political career

780
00:41:33.627 --> 00:41:34.996
over doing the right thing
yesterday?

781
00:41:35.129 --> 00:41:37.164
Oh. I totally chose
my dad's political career.

782
00:41:37.298 --> 00:41:39.400
Ed Carter was a liability.
He had to go.

783
00:41:39.533 --> 00:41:44.005
All that's left is for
my father. outraged at his
one-time contributor's crimes.

784
00:41:44.138 --> 00:41:47.174
to introduce legislation
that will  close every
loophole  Carter Rehab

785
00:41:47.308 --> 00:41:50.878
-was taking advantage of.
-[clicks tongue]
Still think it was me.

786
00:41:51.012 --> 00:41:54.548
-It was not you.
-Okay. If you say so.

787
00:41:54.682 --> 00:41:56.517
♪ <i>One more day to wake</i> ♪

788
00:41:57.918 --> 00:42:00.054
♪ <i>One more step to take</i> ♪

789
00:42:00.921 --> 00:42:02.390
♪ <i>I've got one more...</i> ♪

790
00:42:02.556 --> 00:42:03.724
[R.J. chuckles]

791
00:42:04.191 --> 00:42:06.360
-[phone ringing. buzzing]
-Oh.

792
00:42:06.494 --> 00:42:08.529
♪ <i>One more chain to break</i> ♪

793
00:42:10.164 --> 00:42:11.232
♪ <i>One more day to wake</i> ♪

794
00:42:11.365 --> 00:42:12.666
Hello?

795
00:42:12.800 --> 00:42:14.735
[Mel] <i>Is it too late</i>
<i>to add fries to the order?</i>

796
00:42:14.869 --> 00:42:16.804
Uh. they're closed.
Private event.

797
00:42:16.937 --> 00:42:21.008
I'm gonna try the new taco
place instead. Just text me
when you know what you want.

798
00:42:21.142 --> 00:42:26.814
-♪ <i>I've got one more one more</i> ♪
-♪ <i>One more</i> ♪
